\noindent\textbf{[2024 Oct/Nov, 0580/31, Question 1]}\par

\begin{parts}
\item Write the number six million and thirty in figures.
\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\item Write 7.896 correct to 2 decimal places.
\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\item \[ 8 \quad 24 \quad 25 \quad 36 \quad 39 \quad 41 \quad 48 \]
\relinput{Figures/Q01c.tex}
From this list of numbers, write down
\begin{subparts}
    \item a multiple of 16
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{1}

    \item a factor of 24
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{1}

    \item a cube number
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{1}

    \item a prime number.
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{1}
\end{subparts}

\item Put one pair of brackets into this calculation to make it correct.
\[ 10 - 12 \div 4 + 2 = 8 \]
\Marks{1}

\item By writing each number in the calculation correct to 1 significant figure, find an estimate for the value of
\[ \frac{596 \times 0.047}{8.65} \]
You must show all your working.
\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\item Calculate $(8 \times 10^6) \times (3 \times 10^{-2})$. \\
Give your answer in standard form.
\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\item $216 = 2^3 \times 3^3$ \\
Write $2160$ as a product of its prime factors.
\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}
