\noindent\textbf{[2024 Oct/Nov, 0580/31, Question 3]}\par

Jack does a survey about cycling.

\begin{parts}
\item The bar chart shows the percentage of people in each age group who use a bicycle.
\relinput{Figures/Q03a.tex}

\begin{subparts}
    \item Write down the percentage of people aged 60 to 69 who use a bicycle.
    \AnswerLine[][\%]
    \Marks{1}

    \item 980 people in the survey are in the 30--39 age group. \\
    Work out how many of these people use a bicycle.
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{2}
\end{subparts}

\item Jack makes 18 cycling trips in one year. \\
Each cycling trip lasts 23 minutes. \\
Find the total time Jack spends cycling in this year. \\
Give your answer in hours and minutes.
\AnswerLine[][$\text{h } \dots \text{ min}$]
\Marks{2}

\item The table shows where 240 people cycle the most.
\relinput{Figures/Q03c.tex}

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|l|c|c|}
\hline
& Number of people & Pie chart sector angle \\ \hline
Roads       & 84               & $126^\circ$            \\ \hline
Cycle paths & 72               &                        \\ \hline
Parks       & 48               &                        \\ \hline
Other       & 36               &                        \\ \hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\begin{subparts}
    \item Complete the table.
    \Marks{2}

    \item Complete the pie chart to show this information.
    \relinput{Figures/Q03cii.tex}
    \Marks{2}
\end{subparts}

\item A bicycle costs \$720. \\
Carlo pays one-fifth of the cost as a deposit. \\
He pays the rest of the money in equal monthly payments of \$16. \\
Work out how many monthly payments Carlo makes.
\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{3}
\end{parts}

