\noindent\textbf{[2024 Oct/Nov, 0580/31, Question 6]}\par

\begin{parts}
\item This is a recipe to make ice cream for 6 people.
\begin{center}
    270~ml cream \\
    270~ml milk \\
    100~g sugar \\
    4 egg yolks
\end{center}
Tom makes ice cream for 10 people.

\begin{subparts}
    \item Work out how much milk he uses.
    \AnswerLine[][\text{ml}]
    \Marks{2}

    \item The mass of all the ingredients Tom uses is 1100~g. \\
    After Tom heats the mixture, this mass reduces by 15\%. \\
    Find the mass of the mixture after heating.
    \AnswerLine[][\text{g}]
    \Marks{2}

    \item Tom lets the mixture cool to 5$^\circ$C. \\
    He then puts it into a freezer to cool to $-18^\circ$C. \\
    Find the difference in these temperatures.
    \AnswerLine[][$^\circ\text{C}$]
    \Marks{1}
\end{subparts}

\item 
\begin{subparts}
    \item In a factory, a machine fills 25~920 tubs of ice cream in 8 hours. \\
    Work out the number of tubs the machine fills in 1 minute.
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{1}

    \item A pack of ice cream contains 6 tubs. \\
    There are 120 packs on a tray. \\
    There are 24 trays on a truck. \\
    Work out how many tubs of ice cream are on the truck.
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{1}
\end{subparts}

\item Mario sells ice creams in five flavours. \\
The table shows the relative frequency of some of the ice cream flavours Mario sells.
\relinput{Figures/Q06c.tex}

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|l|c|c|c|c|c|}
\hline
& Vanilla & Chocolate & Strawberry & Coconut & Banana \\ \hline
Relative frequency & 0.34 & & 0.18 & 0.12 & \\ \hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

Mario sells three times as many chocolate ice creams as banana ice creams.

\begin{subparts}
    \item Complete the table.
    \Marks{3}

    \item One week Mario sells 450 ice creams. \\
    Find how many strawberry ice creams Mario expects to sell.
    \AnswerLine[][]
    \Marks{1}

    \item The probability that any customer is an adult is 0.7.
    \begin{subsubparts}
        \item Complete the tree diagram.
        \relinput{Figures/Q06ciii.tex}
        \Marks{1}

        \item Find the probability that the first two customers are adults.
        \AnswerLine[][]
        \Marks{2}
    \end{subsubparts}
\end{subparts}
\end{parts}

